OL,3,CCall for inquiry into growing
OL,4,Cintimidation against MPs
OL,6,FThis would effectively be a cross-
OL,7,Fparty inquiry, led by the Speaker
OL,8,FLindsay Hoyle, into how to guarantee
OL,9,Fthat MPs can go about their work
OL,10,Fwithout threat, harassment or
OL,11,Fviolence.JHarman argued that if
OL,12,Fintimidation is resulting in MPs not
OL,13,Fspeaking in debates or signing motions
OL,14,Fthen it is "undermining democracy".
OL,16,FShe and Ken Clarke - back when he was
OL,17,Fthe father of the House - had
OL,18,Frecommended this in the past but she
OL,19,Fsaid: "The case for it has only got
OL,20,Fstronger"
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/18
