OL,6,FAlthough the idea that this is somehow
OL,7,Fbeing driven by Muslims is simply
OL,8,Fwrong - and the levels of Islamophobia
OL,9,Fon social media that seem to have been
OL,10,Funleashed - deeply worrying.
OL,12,FKeir Starmer was trying to avoid a
OL,13,Fhuge rebellion in the Commons this week
OL,15,FBut it is also true that he felt that
OL,16,Fallowing Labour MPs to express their
OL,17,Fsupport for a ceasefire (which many
OL,18,Fwould not have done if only the SNP
OL,19,Fmotion had stood because they
OL,20,Fdisagreed with some of the language)
OL,21,Fwould reduce levels of abuse.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G7/18
