OL,6,F"The pressure, the workload, the
OL,7,Fcollective abuse is so great on MPs
OL,8,Fnow, I often think I would question
OL,9,Fwhether I would want to be an MP if I
OL,10,Fwas starting out again today," he said.
OL,12,F"It is intolerable."
OL,14,FHe argued that "the language, the
OL,15,Frhetoric, the tone on any issue really
OL,16,Fmatters now", suggesting that while
OL,17,FMPs may have had walkouts of the
OL,18,FChamber in the 1970s they weren't as
OL,19,Finstant and dramatic as now, with
OL,20,Feveryone watching live.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G12/18
